Part 1: Node.js/TypeScript Express API Route
This backend route utilizes the official @aws-sdk/client-s3 (v3) to securely stream an uploaded image file directly into AWS S3, constructs the public CloudFront URL, and updates your PostgreSQL database using pg.

npm install express multer @aws-sdk/client-s3 pg
npm install --save-dev @types/express @types/multer @types/pg

Place file Here ... src/routes/treeUpload.ts

Part 2: React Dashboard Map Integration (Leaflet & Mapbox)

This component merges React-Leaflet for general open-source UI layers with Mapbox Vector Tiles to display background satellite topography seamlessly.The custom marker parses your string-based "Lat, Long" coordinates array on-the-fly and pops open an informative dashboard modal window containing the CloudFront field photo when clicked.

npm install react-leaflet leaflet
npm install --save-dev @types/leaflet

Place file here ... src/components/TreeDashboardMap.tsx
